  "notes": "BlackSky's Gen-2 smallsats (Global 1-19 numbering). eoPortal EO spec backfill (2026-07-09) from the BlackSky Constellation mission page: each Gen-2 satellite carries the SV-24 (Spaceview-24) imaging telescope at 1 m spatial resolution (at 500 km), panchromatic and color imagery, with a planned constellation revisit of a few hours or less; image frames are 30 km2 (frame area, not a swath), so swath_km left null. Page last updated Jul 2, 2025. Weekly maintenance 2026-07-13: status null-filled from the same eoPortal page ('currently contains 19 operational microsatellites'). orbit deliberately left null: the same page's stated altitude/inclination ('Sun-synchronous orbits, altitudes 430-701 km, inclinations 42-59 degrees') is physically inconsistent (a single sun-synchronous orbit does not span that inclination range) and conflicts with the fleet parent's own first-party description of a 'mid-inclination low Earth orbit'; flagging rather than writing a contradictory figure.",
